# Notebook build: run and verify

When a plan includes building or implementing a Jupyter notebook, the task is **not complete** until all of the following are done.

## 1. Execute the notebook

- After implementing the notebook, **run it** (e.g. `jupyter nbconvert --execute --to notebook --inplace <path>` or equivalent).
- Do not treat “notebook written” as done without at least one full run.

## 2. Debug until it runs

- If execution fails: fix the cause (syntax, imports, paths, APIs, data types), then **re-run**.
- Repeat until the notebook runs from top to bottom with no execution errors.

## 3. Verify outputs

- Confirm that all outputs promised in the plan exist:
  - Figures written to the agreed paths (e.g. `output/`).
  - Tables/files (e.g. FITS, ECSV, summary) written to the agreed paths.
- If the plan included “basic checks” or assertions, ensure they pass (or document why they don’t).

## 4. Definition of done

The user should be able to open the notebook and see executed cells, and open/inspect the generated output files. Consider the task complete only when that is true.
